Santander in Talks to Sell 51% of Insurance Unit, Expansion Says

-- B y   S h a r o n   S m y t h
-- 
2011-03-22T06:25:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-22/santander-in-talks-to-sell-51-of-insurance-unit-expansion-says.html
Banco Santander SA (SAN)  is in talks with
a large international insurance company to sell 51 percent of
its Spanish insurance and pensions business, Expansion said
without citing anyone.  The unit has 13.2 billion euros ($18.8 billion) in
insurance policies and 9 billion euros in pensions,  Expansion 
said.  -- Editor: James Kraus  To contact the reporters on this story:
Sharon Smyth in Madrid at 
 ssmyth2@bloomberg.net ;  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Blackman at 
 ablackman@bloomberg.net . 